{"id":42089,"date":"2024-08-18T15:06:53","date_gmt":"2024-08-18T11:06:53","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=42089"},"modified":"2024-08-18T15:07:17","modified_gmt":"2024-08-18T11:07:17","slug":"no-faith-adulterer","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2024\/08\/18\/no-faith-adulterer\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Iman: No faith in adulterer, thief, drunkard, or killer"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>The servant does not commit adultery while he is a believer. He does not steal while he is a believer. He does not drink wine while he is a believer. He does not murder while he is a believer.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>\u2018Ikramah said, \u201cI said to Ibn Abbas: How is faith taken from him?\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cLike so,\u201d and he clasped his fingers together and separated them, \u201cIf he repents, it returns like so,\u201d and he clasped his fingers together.<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6809<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u064a\u064e\u0632\u0652\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064f \u062d\u0650\u064a\u0646\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0632\u0652\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0648\u064e\u0647\u064f\u0648\u064e \u0645\u064f\u0624\u0652\u0645\u0650\u0646\u064c \u0648\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627 \u064a\